Do not use icons that are not understood to mean the same thing by users of your product. An unconventional icon will make your product harder to use, so carefully consider whether you need to use one at all.

### Use a label
Always use an icon with a text label. Using icons on their own can require the user to think more, especially if the icon is not familiar to them.

### Use icons before text to show function
Use an icon *before* the text to help the user understand the function of the element when scanning the page, without needing to fully read the text.

For example, the printer icon on the [print button](#print) quickly shows the user at a glance that they can print what’s on the page.

